content: Hi @T-compiler/meeting . We do not have any meeting proposals. I see a couple different potential options for how to use the hour of time: 1. cancel the meeting itself. 2. re-dedicate the time to discussion of the unstable fingerprint checking that unexpectedly was part of 1.52
I'm not sure how useful (2) will be (e.g., if @Aaron Hill is around or not)

Actually, I guess there doesn’t need to be much of a decision there. I’m going to cancel the meeting, but request that any one who is interested in discussing the follow-through on the fingerprint checking, they should do so in the corresponding (pre-existing) zulip topic: #t-compiler > unstable fingerprints - actually in 1.52
